snippet: The announcement on Friday was at odds both with analysts’ predictions and the experience of Algeria’s neighbors in the wake of last year’s Arab Spring.
abstract: Algeria's governing party the National Liberation Front gains almost half the seats in Parliament, dampening the hopes that the vote might bolster the standing of opposition voices.
lead_paragraph: The announcement on Friday was at odds both with analysts’ predictions and the experience of Algeria’s neighbors in the wake of last year’s Arab Spring.

headline.seo: Algerians Skeptical of Election Results Favoring Party in Power
